history.content: Nope. When you decided to use the swap, your waitlist position was contingent on your decision to go "one or the other". Now that you've changed your mind, the only way to cancel the swap is to drop and re-enroll (even that doesn't work sometimes, unfortunately).

In phase 1 I requested a swap between classes A and B. I'm enrolled in A and waitlisted on B but A currently has a waitlist. I want to be in both classes, so is there any way for me to cancel the swap without losing my place on B's waitlist (if I drop and reenroll in B) or being put on A's waitlist (if I drop and reenroll in A)?
history.subject: Cancelling swap without losing place in waitlist
